## 🧠 About / Bio

### Short Bio (Hero / Meta)
> Full-stack engineer & designer crafting luxury web products for global brands.

### Medium Bio (About Page intro)
> I'm Meet — a 19-year-old full-stack engineer and product designer based in Ahmedabad, India. I started building software at 16, joined AS Technolabs as a Unity developer, and grew into full-stack web development by teaching myself React, Next.js, and cloud infrastructure on the side.
>
> I design in Figma first, build with modern stacks, and use agentic tools like Cursor to ship fast without sacrificing quality. My work spans luxury ecommerce, SaaS platforms, and interactive web applications — always built for international markets.

### Long Bio (Full About Page)
> I'm Meet — a 19-year-old full-stack engineer and designer based in Ahmedabad, India. I write this not to impress, but to be honest about where I'm coming from and where I'm going.
>
> I grew up in a single-mother household. My father left when I was one. That background didn't slow me down — it built the self-discipline I rely on every single day. At 16, while most of my peers were still figuring things out, I landed my first professional role as a Unity developer at AS Technolabs. I've been there nearly three years now, and my role has grown from building game mechanics to architecting full-stack web products.
>
> Today I work across the entire stack — React, Next.js, Node.js, MongoDB, AWS EC2, TypeScript — and I design everything in Figma before a single line of code gets written. I use agentic coding tools like Cursor to move fast, but I never ship something I don't fully understand.
>
> My long-term goal is to build SaaS and AI products for international markets. Every project I take on right now is a step in that direction — building the portfolio, the process, and the reputation to get there.

### One-liner (Footer / Cards)
> Crafting digital experiences that inspire and convert.

